To all my friendos and buddos:

As many of you are hearing back from the departments there is something I want to make absolutely clear: you are not your major. Your worth as a person is not dictated by where you go to school, what you do as a career, or even a few bad decisions. As you all know, major decisions will be coming out soon. If you get in, congratulations! I am very proud of you, you should be happy to see all that you've accomplished! And if not, please understand that it does not mean you are any less of a wonderful person.

I find it disheartening and disappointing how people in the UW community go out of their way to put down others for what they are passionate about. I've met individuals who work two jobs, or even night shifts just to pay for their education and chase their dreams. To be met with attitudes of condescension is incredibly unkind and mean spirited.

I wish you all the best of luck! If you are upset or feeling down, please feel free to reach out to me. I hope to do my best to encourage and affirm you! Let's make a conscious effort to leave our communities in a better place than we left it! <3 Stay W H O L E S O M E
